@startuml ct_api_observability
' ============================================================
' Title:     nasim — Observability API
' Boundary:  NASIM Application — HTTPAdapter API surface
' Purpose:   Public interfaces for structured logging, metrics, trace, and redaction
' Milestone: v1.0
' Version:   1.0.0
' Source:    docs/audit/audit.2026.06.20.logging.observability.car.md
' Review:    —
' Note:      Emit-only per tenas pattern. nasim never pulls/queries logs.
' ============================================================

title nasim — Observability API

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

package "Observability API" #E3F2FD {

    interface "StructuredLogger" <<interface>> {
        + emit(record : LogRecord) : None
        + debug(msg : str, **extra) : None
        + info(msg : str, **extra) : None
        + warning(msg : str, **extra) : None
        + error(msg : str, **extra) : None
        + exception(msg : str, exc : Exception) : None
    }

    interface "MetricsCollector" <<interface>> {
        + counter(name : str, labels : dict) : Counter
        + gauge(name : str, labels : dict) : Gauge
        + histogram(name : str, labels : dict) : Histogram
        + record_llm_request(model : str, provider : str, latency_ms : float, tokens : int) : None
        + record_tool_call(tool : str, success : bool, duration_ms : float) : None
        + record_error(error_type : str) : None
    }

    interface "TraceCorrelator" <<interface>> {
        + new_trace(operation : str) : TraceContext
        + current_span() : TraceContext
        + child_span(operation : str) : TraceContext
        + span_id() : str
        + trace_id() : str
    }

    interface "ContextPropagator" <<interface>> {
        + propagate() : dict
        + inject(headers : dict) : dict
        + extract(headers : dict) : TraceContext
    }

    interface "LogRedactor" <<interface>> {
        + redact(record : LogRecord) : LogRecord
        + redact_payload(payload : dict) : dict
        + add_rule(rule : RedactionRule) : None
        + remove_rule(pattern : str) : None
    }

    interface "DualOutputAdapter" <<interface>> {
        + emit(record : LogRecord) : None
        + is_tty() : bool
    }

    interface "OTelExporter" <<interface>> {
        + start_span(operation : str) : Span
        + record_metric(point : MetricPoint) : None
        + flush() : None
        + shutdown() : None
    }
}

note bottom of StructuredLogger
  Facade over structlog + JSON formatter.
  emit writes one JSON line to stdout per record.
  Convenience methods (debug/info/warning/error)
  construct LogRecord with trace context from TraceCorrelator.
  Never ships, buffers, or forwards — emit only.
end note

note bottom of MetricsCollector
  Facade over prometheus-client.
  counter/gauge/histogram return metric handles.
  Convenience methods instrument key nasim events:
  LLM requests, tool calls, errors.
  /metrics endpoint served by ServerApp (HTTP mode)
  or printed on demand (CLI mode).
end note

note bottom of TraceCorrelator
  Generates and binds trace context via contextvars.
  new_trace creates root span for CLI turn or HTTP request.
  child_span creates nested spans for provider calls, tool exec.
  All spans carry trace_id + span_id for correlation.
end note

note right of ContextPropagator
  Propagates trace context across boundaries:
  - Provider calls (headers)
  - Tool dispatch (explicit passing)
  - Subagent spawn (spawn message)
  - MCP tool calls (standard headers if SSE)
  ensure every log record and wire event
  carries correlation ids.
end note

note right of LogRedactor
  Regex-based secret stripping.
  Always on — cannot be disabled.
  Applied before emission to both structured and wire.
  Configurable rules: global + per-project.
  Patterns: env vars, API keys, .env content, passwords.
end note

note bottom of DualOutputAdapter
  CLI entry adapter for dual output.
  JSON always written to stdout (machine).
  Rich human output delegated to Renderer when isatty.
  HTTP/MCP bypass this adapter (direct structured emission).
  Semantics never change based on output mode.
end note

note bottom of OTelExporter
  Optional — behind otel feature flag.
  Bridges TraceCorrelator spans to OTel SDK.
  Exports via OTLP/gRPC or stdout.
  Zero dependency cost when feature disabled.
  Enables distributed tracing in production deployments.
end note

@enduml
